Defendant Cedric D Dailey in court with attorney Craig S. Powell.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 1 YEAR in the House of Corrections, with credit for 5 days time served, with Huber release privileges for work only; No electronic monitoring; with the following conditions:

-Restitution set at $0
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges due during term of probation; if defendant is revoked, cost, surcharges and assessments due within 6 months of revocation;  nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-No association with drug users, drug dealers, drug houses and otherwise engage in drug dealing
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain employment unless in school.  If in school full-time, defendant to have a part-time job; if defendant in school part-time defendant to have a full time job
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-No contact with 2344 N. 58th Street
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-As a condition of probation, defendant to serve 75 days in the House of Corrections, 60 days to be served with Huber release privedges and release to attend programs he is participating in.  No good time release privileges;  No electronic monitoring.  Defendant to report to the House of Corrections on June 18, 2015 by 12:00 noon.  15 days of this sentence is STAYED to be used at the discretion of the probation agent.  

Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms or body armor; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.

Filed, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement
